1 Model comparison

1.1 Test on arm_smk0

  • Null model arm:

\(var(y) = \sigma_{g}^2 A + \sigma_{e}^2 I\)

  • Alternative model arm_smk0

\(var(y) = \sigma_{g}^2 A + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\)

  • Difference in the number of parameters (df in the LRT test): 1

1.2 Test on arm_by_smk_vareq

  • Null model arm_smk0

\(var(y) = \sigma_{g}^2 A + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\)

  • Alternative model arm_by_smk_vareq

\(var(y) = \sigma^2_{g} \begin{pmatrix} A & \rho_g A\\ \rho_g A & A \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\)

  • Difference in the number of parameters (df in the LRT test): 1
trait stat pval
FEV1_FVC_utah NA NA
FEV1pp_utah NA NA
FEV1_utah NA NA
FVCpp_utah NA NA
FVC_utah NA NA
log_pctEmph_Slicer NA NA
TLCpp_race_adjusted NA NA

1.3 Test on arm_by_smk

  • Null model arm_smk0

\(var(y) = \sigma_{g}^2 A + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\)

  • Alternative model arm_by_smk

\(var(y) = \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{g1}^2 A & \rho_g \sigma_{g1} \sigma_{g2} A\\ \rho_g \sigma_{g1} \sigma_{g2} A & \sigma_{g2}^2 A \end{pmatrix} + \begin{pmatrix} \sigma_{e1}^2 I & 0 \\ 0 & \sigma_{e2}^2 I \end{pmatrix}\)

  • Difference in the number of parameters (df in the LRT test): 2
trait stat pval
TLCpp_race_adjusted 0.2666266 0.87519086
FEV1_FVC_utah 1.1862229 0.55260521

FVCpp_utah 5.4145500 0.06671837
